# UI Select Standard

All dropdown / list-picker UI must use `@/components/ui/Select`. Do **not** use native `<select>` / `<option>` — browser menus break visual consistency (RTL chevron, focus ring, menu shadow, centered status lists).

## Component

```tsx
import { Select } from "@/components/ui/Select";
```

## Variants

| `variant` | When to use |
|-----------|-------------|
| `default` | General forms, filters, hub pickers |
| `status` | Workflow status fields (e.g. design / print status) — centered list + checkmark |
| `pill` | Document status badges with per-option tone via `getOptionClassName` |

## Accents

Match surrounding section color: `pink` (default), `cyan`, `amber`, `purple`, `fuchsia`, `emerald`.

## Common props

- `clearable={false}` when a value is always required
- `textAlign="center"` for status-style lists
- `size="sm"` in dense tables
- `buttonClassName` / `menuClassName` only to align with local layout — keep tokens from `globals.css`

## Examples in codebase

- `StyledStatusSelect` in `app/dashboard/trip/[id]/plan/page.tsx` — status + pill wrappers
- `RuleSelect` in `app/manager/settings/required-roles/page.tsx` — settings forms
- `ParticipantsTab.tsx` — `accent="pink"`

When adding a new dropdown, extend `Select` props if the pattern is reusable; do not fork a one-off menu.
